The article is a transcript of a speech given by the First Lady, Jill Biden, and President Joe Biden at an event honoring Sir Elton John. The event was organized by A&E and aimed to celebrate Elton John's music and his contributions to various causes, including HIV/AIDS awareness and LGBTQ+ rights. The First Lady and President Biden thanked Elton John for his advocacy and presented him with the National Humanities Medal. Elton John expressed gratitude for the award and pledged to continue his efforts in fighting AIDS. The President also mentioned the government's commitment to allocate $6 billion towards HIV/AIDS initiatives.